Get together all your best photos and show everyone what you have to celebrate!



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Word to Your Holiday
description:
If a 90's hip-hop singer gave Christmas Cards...

He might like this one.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Flannel Suit
description:
Nothing feels quite as classy as a brand new pinstripe suit.

Tell your loved ones how classy you are, with this awesomely subtle holiday greeting. (or....show how on this ONE DAY everyone got dressed up and pretended to have it all together)



Photography courtesy
Foto Fly

name: Be Merry
description:
Being merry is one of my favorite feelings of the season. It's just a happy time.

Show everyone what you have to be merry about with this fun and modern card.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Purple Presents
description:
Sometimes the wrapping is as good as the gift inside it.

Send this elegant mustard and purple damask card to everyone you know this year. They'll think you're fancy.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Merry Modern Christmas
description:
This one kinda reminds me of a "foggy christmas eve" Don't you think that yummy raspberry greeting could be Rudolph's nose?

Obviously I put WAY too much interpretation into this job.



Photography courtesy
Foto Fly

name: Figgie Pudding
description:
What even IS figgie pudding? I'll admit. I don't know.

But I do know that I love this deep plum color to send out my holiday greeting.

And I will totally stay at your house until you bring me some Figgie Pudding. Unless it's gross. Then chocolate will do.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Right in Line
description:
This fabulous greeting card looks amazing with all the warm tones of the season.

It also features multiple spaces to show off all your great shots.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Stripes of Green
description:
Green is one of the most traditional colors of the season. But when you pair it up with this earthy neutral color, it brings such an awesome feeling to it.

Plus, if I think about green, maybe the snow will go away the day after Christmas...and bring me my flowers back! No? What? Boo!



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Snowy Lace
description:
This card is both contemporary and vintage. Kind of a mixed bag.

I admit, I do LOVE it with a black & white photo. It just makes the yellow color pop off the page.

But you certainly could add your color photo as well.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Snowstorm
description:
I love a holiday card that comes with unexpected colors.

Distinguish yourself from the pack with this modern card all the joy of the season, without the predictable colors.



Photography courtesy
Moment 2 Moment Photography

name: 'Tis the Season
description:
The warm and neutral tones of this card make me want to curl up in front of a fire.

I have some awesome fuzzy slippers I could wear.

Wait. This was about you and your card...wasn't it? Oops. You'll love this one. I do.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Ornamental Holiday
description:
This fun and bright setting is a great way to show off ALL of your amazing pics.

Black & White pictures pop right off the page next to the bright red and green.

And there's plenty of room to add pictures of everyone.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Contempo Holiday
description:
I'm kind of in love with the turquoise and red combo. And this contemporary pairing is no exception.

Add some fun colors to your greeting this holiday season!



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Holidays in a Row
description:
Possibly one of my favorite cards I've EVER designed.

"Holidays in a Row" just brings a certain cheerfulness to your celebration.

You'll love sending this one out to the people you care about.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: To You From Us
description:
Take your fabulous offset pictures and decorate them with a fabulous ornament!

I love the popping red ornament on this card. This card was the one our family actually sent out. So you KNOW I love it!



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Argyle Noel
description:
This has to be one of my very favorite holiday cards. And not just because it reminds me of yummy warm socks and sitting by the fire.

I love the argyle pattern, and the completely unexpected colors.

Put on some socks, and order one today!

name: Holiday With Class
description:
Black & white. Does it get any classier?

Always a winning combo, this black and white card will look great with a color photo as well.

Make your holiday a black-tie affair, with this upscale greeting. (don't forget your tuxedo!)



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Joyful
description:
This all-grown-up card expresses one of the most beautiful sentiments of the season.

I love the dark navy and the burst of red.

It certainly makes me feel joyful.

name: Peppermint Twist
description:
I can almost smell the peppermint coming from this super fun greeting!

The bright red and white are one of my favorite holiday combos. And add that minty green? It's just fresh.

This one would be awesome with a Black & white photo as well.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Decorated Season
description:
This awesomely unexpected card has to be one of my faves in the whole shop! It's just so much fun.

Works particularly well with an offset photo.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: We Wish You
description:
I love the mix of bright color and houndstooth on this card.

It makes me want to spray some artificial pine smell and have a cup of chocolate.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Gift in the Box
description:
This card reminds me of a bunch of gift boxes sitting under the tree.

I love the bright pops of color, next to a cheery family photo. Nothing says The Holidays like a cup of cheer!



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Jingle Bells
description:
Drawing inspiration from one of the season's most beloved tunes, this card will get your friends singing along.

And getting that tune stuck in your head? Well....it's kinda like the Barney song, you can't stop singing it. But that's not your problem. Is it?

Your loved ones can just thank you later.



Photography courtesy
Pink Daffodil Photography

name: Sweet & Sugar
description:

The bright colors on this card remind me of all the bright colors that sugar comes in at this time of year.

This one is awesome with a black & white photo.
